        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 10:46PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 1046 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bronson, or 15 miles east of La Harpe, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Scott, Marmaton, Bronson, Uniontown, Fulton, Redfield, Mapleton,
Hammond, Devon, Harding, and Xenia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
